01:38:10,200 --> 01:38:16,360
to hire him on as an assistant curator. By all accounts, the pay was unimpressive,

1044
01:38:16,360 --> 01:38:21,160
but it did not dampen Smith's enthusiasm for the job. Soon, he was working long hours,

1045
01:38:21,160 --> 01:38:26,840
piecing together Kinneathorn tablets for transcription. In 1866, he published his

1046
01:38:26,840 --> 01:38:31,720
first article, and the next year Rawinson had the museum hire him on as his assistant for

1047
01:38:31,720 --> 01:38:38,040
the future volumes of Kinneathorn inscriptions. As Smith himself would describe it, this hiring

