01:38:44,200 --> 01:38:49,640
excavating in Mesopotamia himself went unrealized, and he was unable to convince the university

1050
01:38:49,640 --> 01:38:55,880
trustees to finance such an expedition. Indeed, by this point, many of them felt that the museum

1051
01:38:55,880 --> 01:39:00,280
already had enough of what they dubbed primitive Babylonian and Assyrian artifacts.

1052
01:39:01,880 --> 01:39:07,720
Then in November of 1872, whilst working on volume four of Rawinson's series, Smith was

1053
01:39:07,720 --> 01:39:12,760
sorting through a group of tablets that had laid untranscribed in the museum archives for the last

